<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>paregorios.org (Posts about htaccess)</title><link>https://paregorios.org/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://paregorios.org/categories/htaccess.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Contents Â© 2018 &lt;a href="mailto:paregorios@hotmail.com"&gt;Tom Elliott&lt;/a&gt; </copyright><lastBuildDate>Mon, 09 Apr 2018 16:22:02 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Hosting Quest</title><link>https://paregorios.org/posts/2018/04/hosting_quest/</link><dc:creator>Tom Elliott</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I'm currently hosting &lt;em&gt;paregorios.org&lt;/em&gt; via GitHub pages, but I'm looking for an alternative because there are features I need that GitHub doesn't provide. Here, I think, is a description of my ideal solution:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apache web server with ability to use &lt;code&gt;.htaccess&lt;/code&gt; files (because I want to be able to issue HTTP redirects)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SSL with Let's Encrypt&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deploy via ssh+rsync using ssh keys&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cost: less than $10/month&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I wonder where I will be able to find such a combination.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>apache</category><category>hosting</category><category>htaccess</category><category>rsync</category><category>ssh</category><category>ssl</category><guid>https://paregorios.org/posts/2018/04/hosting_quest/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 08 Apr 2018 19:49:31 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>